<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--HolidayBabies     11-29 0130</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Holiday Babies,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Couple Has Third Holiday Baby</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INDIANOLA, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Some people celebrate April Fool's Day by
playing pranks, St. Patrick's Day with a toast to the Irish and
Thanksgiving Day with a turkey. Sandy Moore has celebrated all three
by having babies.
   Mrs. Moore, 33, of Indiana Township gave birth to Jason, 9
pounds, 1 ounce, on Thanksgiving Day in West Penn Hospital in
Pittsburgh.
   Mother and baby were doing fine.
   Jason is the third holiday baby for Mrs. Moore and her 33
year-old husband, Martin.
   Their oldest child, Amanda, arrived on April Fool's Day 1982, and
their second child, Jacquelyn, was born in St. Patrick's Day 1984.
   Mrs. Moore attributes the birthdays to luck.
   ``All this has made me really happy,'' she said Monday night.
</TEXT>
