<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0435</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow Scattered East and West; High Winds in California</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell in the Northeast, Midwest and West today and high winds
whipped across southern California.
   Rain and snow showers that were scattered across the Northeast
formed ahead of a cold front entering the lower Great Lakes region
and northern New England.
   A snow advisory was posted for the mountains and northwestern
sections of Pennsylvania. The Laurel Mountains of Pennsylvania had
about 2 inches of snow by early today.
   Elswhere, a cold front caused snow and high winds in Colorado,
prompting advisories for snow and blowing snow in the northern and
central mountains of the state. Up to 8 inches of snow was expected.
   Snow showers were scattered from the central High Plains across
the middle Missouri Valley.
   Santa Ana winds up to 60 mph led to a high wind warning in
southern California.
   Much of the Northwest was cloudy, and light rain was scattered
along the coast.
   Clear skies prevailed from California through the southern Plains
to the southern Atlantic Coast.
   Today's forecast called for snow scattered from the upper Great
Lakes into the lower Missouri Valley and over northern Maine; and
rainshowers over northwest Washington state.
   Highs should be in the 20s from the upper Mississippi Valley into
upper Michigan; 50s and 60s from the central California Coast across
the southern Rockies, west central and northern Texas, Arkansas and
the lower Mississippi Valley to the southern Atlantic Coast; 70s
over southern California, southwest Arizona, south central Texas and
southern Florida; and 30s to 40s across most of the rest of the
nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 10
degrees at Hibbing, Minn., to 70 at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 34 fair; Boston 40 windy; Buffalo 37 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C., 41 fair; Cincinnati 25 fair; Cleveland 31
cloudy; Detroit 31 fair; Miami 64 cloudy; New York 39 windy;
Philadelphia 38 fair; Pittsburgh 32 windy; Portland 38 fair;
Washington 40 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 26 fair; Chicago 27 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 47
windy; Denver 35 fair; Des Moines 34 cloudy; Indianapolis 25 fair;
Kansas City 37 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 21 cloudy; Nashville 28
fair; New Orleans 40 fair; St. Louis 35 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 34 fair; Anchorage 13 fair; Las Vegas 50 fair;
Los Angeles 55 fair; Phoenix 51 fair; Salt Lake City 31 partly
cloudy; San Diego 53 fair; San Francisco 51 fair; Seattle 42 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 34 fair; Toronto 36 partly cloudy.
