<1ST_LINE>r i PM-India-Accident     11-29 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-India-Accident,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jet's Nosewheel Collapses, Six Injured</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto DEL1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nosewheel of an Indian Airlines
jetliner collapsed today as passengers were leaving the aircraft at
New Delhi's Indira Gandhi airport. At least six people were injured.
   The condition of one of the injured passengers was serious,
airline officials said.
   The front belly of the Airbus A-300 was severely damaged, United
News of India reported.
   An Indian Airlines official, speaking on condition of anonymity,
said the nosewheel collapsed as the front door of the jet was opened
and passengers began to disembark.
   The plane had carried 268 passengers and crew from the western
city of Bombay. Most passengers still were aboard when the accident
occurred.
   An Indian Airlines Boeing 737 crashed at Ahmedabad airport Oct.
19, killing 133 people. The crash sparked debates in Parliament,
with some politicians accusing the airline of poor maintenance.
</TEXT>
