<HEAD>Three Die in Fire That Sweeps Through Isolated Town</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LEGAZPI, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A wind-driven fire swept through a
coastal town on southeastern Luzon island Tuesday, killing three
people and destroying hundreds of houses, officials said.
   Mayor Macario Pavia said the fire started about 9 a.m. in the
public market of Pio Duran, about 200 miles southeast of Manila.
   Bad roads prevented fire trucks from reaching the town of 35,000
for nearly six hours, Pavia said. The cause of the blaze was not
known.
   Thousands of people who were evacuated from their homes took
refuge in churches and government buildings.
