<1ST_LINE>r w AM-PlaygroundSettlement     11-29 0240</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Playground Settlement,230</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Playground Equipment Maker to Make Repairs, Pay Penalty</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Miracle Recreation Equipment Co. has agreed to
pay a $100,000 civil penalty and to make corrections on several of
the public playground equipment products it sells, the Consumer
Product Safety Commission announced Tuesday.
   The monetary payment settled charges that Miracle failed to
promptly report defects in its Bounce-Around Whirl and Buckaroo
Whirl playground devices, which were subject to a repair program in
1983. Those products had been associated with 70 injuries to the
legs of children, the commission said.
   The new agreement calls for corrections for other products,
including the Flying Animal Swing, which has been blamed for one
death and seven injuries to children struck by the swing, the
commission said.
   Also to be corrected are the Lifetime Whirl, Slashproof Swing
Set, Arch Swing and Therapeutic Whirl, which have been associated
with 50 injuries, according to the safety agency.
   In announcing the settlement, the commission noted that Miracle
has denied that any of its products are defective or that they pose
a substantial risk to children. The company has also denied
violating product reporting rules. In addition, the agency noted
that it has made no formal finding of violations by the company.
   However, the company agreed to notify its customer list of the
settlement and make any repairs necessary.
   Anyone needing more information can contact Miracle at
1-800-523-4202 or the safety commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
