<HEAD>Two People Dead in Shooting At Bagel Restaurant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ski-masked gunman walked into a bagel
restaurant and opened fire today, killing two people and critically
wounding a third, then escaped from the shop safely, police said.
   Albuquerque Police Sgt. Ruth Lowe said a man walked into the
Bagel Lovers restaurant about 9 a.m. and started shooting. A witness
told police that the gunman had paced back and forth in front of the
shop before he went in, she said.
   One man was dead at the scene, she said. The other, a 63-year-old
man, died at University of New Mexico Hospital with a gunshot wound
to the head, said hospital spokesman Bob Hlady.
   The woman was in critical condition at the hospital, also wounded
in the head.
   ``We don't have any motive at all,'' Lowe said. ``We have a very
slight description.''
   Police said they were looking for a white man in his early 30s
about 5-foot-5 to 6-foot tall. They said the man was wearing a ski
mask.
