<HEAD>Excerpts of Gorbachev Address</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Soviet, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Excerpts from President Mikhail S. Gorbachev's
address on political reform Tuesday to the Supreme Soviet:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   No, comrades, there are no easy ways. I have had many occasions
to say that it is only by combining economic reform with political
changes, democratization and glasnost that we can fulfil both the
immediate and long-term tasks we have set ourselves.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   The principal content of the first stage of the reform is
streamlining the structure of soviets, the order of the formation
and the activity of the supreme bodies of power and the electoral
system. The draft laws submitted for discussion to this session are
aimed to achieve precisely that .... The next major stage of
political transformation will be linked with the harmonization of
relations between the union and its constituent republics.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Separate mention should be made of pronouncements in favor of
broader and far-reaching changes in the Constitution of the U.S.S.R.
This applies to a radical rewording of the preamble, a new
interpretation of socialist pro socialism with democracy and
on this basis tapping the entire potential of our social system, we
have no right to forget even for one minute that socialist
democracy, like any democracy, has nothing in common with lack of
discipline, egoism and anarchy.
