<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ActorShoots     11-29 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Actor Shoots,0200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Aspiring Actor Accidentally Shoots Self In `Lethal Weapon' Scene</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An aspiring actor re-enacting a
scene from the movie ``Lethal Weapon'' accidentally shot himself in
the mouth in front of horrified fellow students, police said.
   Adam Smith Hancock, 22, of suburban Tujunga, was in critical
condition Tuesday at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, said hospital
spokesman Ron Wise.
   Hancock placed the barrel of the weapon in his mouth, pulled the
trigger and fell to the stage during the scene Monday afternoon at
the American Legion Hall, part of an actors' workshop from the
Beverly Hills Playhouse.
   ``There is no evidence at this time that it was a suicide
attempt,'' said police Lt. Bob Curtis. ``But the gun, a .22-caliber
semi-automatic handgun, belonged to him and was loaded with live
ammunition.''
   In a similar shooting four years ago, actor Jon-Erik Hexum picked
up a weapon loaded with blanks, put the barrel to his head and
pulled the trigger on the set of the ``Cover-Up'' television series.
Wadding from the blank cartridge was driven into his skull and Hexum
died six days later.
   That shooting on Oct. 12, 1984, was ruled accidental.
</TEXT>
