<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Harper,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Valerie Harper Signs With CBS</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Valerie Harper, who left an NBC series in a
contract dispute last year, will star in a new series on CBS, the
network announced Tuesday.
   After Harper left ``Valerie,'' Sandy Duncan was brought in and
the show renamed ``The Hogan Family.''
   Harper sued Lorimar Productions and in September was awarded
$1.85 million in damages and a share of the profits from the NBC
show, of which she was part owner.
   Like ``Valerie,'' the CBS show will also be produced by Harper's
AV Productions and will be overseen by her producer husband, Tony
Cacciotti.
   It will be shot at MTM Productions, the site of the show that
launched Harper's career, ``The Mary Tyler Moore Show.'' MTM also
produced the spinoff ``Rhoda,'' in which Harper starred.
   CBS did not yet have a title, premise or planned air date for the
new series. The executive producer is Paul Haggis, who was
responsible for the successful CBS sitcom ``One Day at a Time.''
</TEXT>
