<HEAD>Duchess of York's Slimmer Figure</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Duchess of York won press plaudits Wednesday
for her clearly evident success in beating her weight problem.
   The 29-year-old wife of Prince Andrew showed off her new sleek
figure when she presented the 1988 awards for business sponsors at
London's National Theater on Tuesday.
   She was criticized for having a dumpy figure immediately after
the birth of her daughter Princess Beatrice on Aug. 8.
   But the tabloid Daily Express commented Wednesday: ``Gone were
the excess pounds that had unkind jibes circulating after Princess
Bea's birth in the summer. Instead she seemed almost pencil slim.
   ``Friends say she has been rigorously dieting coupled with
dancing and aerobics.''
   Another tabloid, the Daily Mirror, said: ``The duchess has lost
well over a stone (14 pounds) and is now slimmer than she was before
she had baby Beatrice.''
