<2ND_LINE>AM-Rape Case, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0629,0349</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>12-Year-Old Arrested in Rape of 30-Year-Old Disabled Woman</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with 6 grafs to UPDATE with charges filed, arraignment
scheduled; picks up 6th graf pvs, `Burris said...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>AUBURN, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old boy was charged with
second-degree rape Tuesday in an alleged attack against his former
babysitter, a 30-year-old mentally retarded woman who lived next
door.
   The woman was attacked Sept. 22 at an elementary school across
from her home, said Detective Michael Burris.
   The woman, who has cerebral palsy, lives with her 68-year-old
mother, who said she believed that the boy and possibly others in
the neighborhood beat her daughter with a stick, then raped her.
   ``Three days before this happened, he (the 12-year-old) asked her
for sex,'' the mother said. ``She knew enough to say `No.' He said,
`I'll get you.'''
   The boy was arrested Monday. Detectives were investigating the
mother's belief that other youngsters were involved, Burris said.
   Arraignment was scheduled for Wednesday in juvenile court, with a
detention review to determine whether the boy should remain in
custody.
   Burris said the young woman's fear and limited mental capacity,
plus a lack of physical evidence, hampered the investigation. She
did not tell her mother she had been raped until three weeks after
the alleged attack, the mother said.
   The detective said the woman was able to communicate some details
of the alleged attack, but he wasn't sure whether she would be able
to testify at a trial.
   The boy could receive up to seven months in juvenile detention,
said Dan Donohoe of the King County prosecutor's office.
   The mother said the attack occurred after her daughter went to a
convenience store.
   ``She used to baby-sit the boy when he was little. (He) knew she
was mentally retarded,'' the mother said.
   She said her daughter had ``two great big goose eggs on her head,
and they took a stick and cracked her across the nose. She had black
eyes for two weeks. They beat her legs until her legs were all
pulpy.''
</TEXT>
