<2ND_LINE>AM-Interco,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Interco Mails Cash Portions of Special Dividend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interco Inc. said Tuesday that it had obtained
definitive financing and was mailing the cash portion of the special
dividends it had declared to ward off a $2.7 billion hostile
takeover.
   As announced earlier, the special dividends for the restructuring
and recapitalization amounted to $38.60 per share of Interco common
stock. The company said checks in the amount of $14.221 per share
were being mailed to shareholders of record as of the close of
business on Oct. 13, and checks for $24.379 are being sent to
shareholders of record as of the close of business on Nov. 22.
   Interco said it had been advised by the New York Stock Exchange
that shares of Interco common will trade ``ex-dividend'' with
respect to the cash portions of the special dividends on Wednesday.
   The $2.8 billion Interco restructuring plan was valued by the
company at $76 per share.
   Cardinal Acquisition Corp., headed by brothers Steven M. and
Mitchell P. Rales of Washington, D.C., had mounted a $74-a-share
takeover attempt but the hostile tender offer expired Nov. 16 and
was not extended.
